The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | PC posts
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     PC posts
                            
	New Delhi, Dec. 20: K.C. Verma, a 1971 batch IPS officer of the Jharkhand cadre, was appointed home minister P. Chidambarams internal security adviser today.        
	Verma is secretary (security) in the cabinet secretariat and the new assignment would be an added responsibility. Safi Ahsan Rizvi, an IPS officer of the 1989 cadre from the Intelligence Bureau, has been appointed officer on special duty to the minister.        
	Chidambaram has also chosen Rajeev Kumar Mital, an IAS officer of the 1998 batch of Maharashtra cadre, as his private secretary.         
	The minister has asked for briefings from the IB director twice a day, sources said.                                                                                                                                                                          
